# GitHub token for profile updates
# Use a CLASSIC personal access token: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# Required scopes:
#   repo       - read private repos (language + workflow-run stats)
#   read:user  - include private-repo contribution counts in contributionsCollection
# Note: a fine-grained token has no read:user equivalent and would return public-only data.
# The token must belong to the account whose stats are generated (afisch710).
# In CI this value lives in the PROFILE_UPDATE_TOKEN repo secret; rotate it before it expires
# (an expired token makes the nightly "Refresh GitHub Profile Data" workflow fail).
GITHUB_TOKEN=your_token_here
